critical_issue.description:
lib/db-users.ts DEFINES ITS OWN getSql() function:

```typescript
import { neon } from "@neondatabase/serverless"

function getSql() {
  return neon(process.env.DATABASE_URL!)
}
```

This MUST be removed. The new file must import from ./connection.

step.details:
Copy contents from lib/db-users.ts with these CRITICAL changes:

1. REMOVE the local getSql() function and neon import
2. ADD: `import { getSql } from "./connection"`
3. IMPORT types from "./types": `import type { DashboardUser, Invite } from "./types"`
4. Keep all functions exactly as-is (they use getSql() internally which now comes from connection)

The file should start like:
```typescript
import { getSql } from "./connection"
import type { DashboardUser, Invite } from "./types"

// Re-export types for convenience
export type { DashboardUser, Invite }

// ============================================
// User Queries
// ============================================
// ... rest of code
```
